<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a179182-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s3208"><num value="3208">§ 3208.</num><heading> Relationship to other applicable law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter prohibits any State regulatory authority or nonregulated gas utility from adopting, pursuant to State law, any standard or rule affecting gas utilities which is different from any standard established by this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a179183-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/617/tIII/s308">Pub. L. 95–617, title III, § 308</ref>, <date date="1978-11-09">Nov. 9, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/3153">92 Stat. 3153</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a179184-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id7a179185-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="definitions" id="id7a179186-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Definitions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The definition of State in <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s2602">section 2602 of Title 16</ref>, Conservation, applies to this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
